[[File:Infernal Mage icon.png|left]]
'''Infernal Mages''' are [[slayer monsters]] that require 45 [[Slayer]] to kill. They are sometimes hunted for their frequent drops of [[Death rune|death runes]] and their rare [[Mystic boots (dark)|dark mystic boots]] and [[Mystic hat (dark)|hat]] drops. Players who plan on fighting them should be wary of their accurate magic attack.

==Strengths and weaknesses==
Infernal Mages use a weaker version of the spell [[Fire Blast]] to attack the player, so it is recommended to wear [[dragonhide]] or [[Armour/Magic armour|magic armour]], which will reduce their chance to hit. Wearing [[Void Knight equipment|Void Knight armour]] is a good option because of its high magic defence. The [[Protect from Magic]] prayer is recommended for lower levels, as these mages can hit often. [[Prayer#Prayer Flicking|Prayer flicking]] is an effective strategy to minimise their damage output. Due to their focus on using magic, they are weak to both melee and ranged attacks. They '''cannot''' be safespotted, but it is possible to safely hit-and-run them with ranged (with or without long-ranged depending on the weapon used), or by luring a mage into the south-eastern corridor and then hiding in the south-eastern most alcove of the tower.

